lab4b.c:
    The source code that prints the time and temperature of the beaglebone based on the given period. User is able to use option --scale to change the unit of temperature.
If log option is specifeid, it will record the result to the given file. It takes following commands: 
   SCALE=F-change the temperature unit to Fahrenheit
   SCALE=C-change the temperature unit to Centegrade
   PERIOD=seconds change the period for each time it reports
   STOP= pause the program
   START= continue the program
   LOG line of text = just log whatever it has
   OFF= shutdown the program.


README: The description of all the files

tests.sh:
    Smoke tests, which tests the basic function.

compile.sh:
    a compiling script to compile the code with DUMMY option if it is not on the baglebone. 
Makefile:
    The makefile for compiling, testing, and compressing.


